    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Logistic Regression</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n        }\n        .container {\n            max-width: 500px;\n            margin: 40px auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            background-color: #f9f9f9;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        .header {\n            text-align: center;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n        .header h1 {\n            font-size: 24px;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        .header p {\n            font-size: 18px;\n        }\n        .button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: #fff;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        .button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\">\n            <h1>Logistic Regression</h1>\n            <p>Logistic Regression is a supervised learning algorithm used for binary classification problems.</p>\n        </div>\n        <p>Logistic Regression is a type of linear regression that uses logistic function to model the relationship between the input features and the target variable.</p>\n        <div id=\"result\"></div>\n        <script>\n            // Sample data\n            let X = [\n                [0, 0],\n                [0, 1],\n                [1, 0],\n                [1, 1]\n            ];\n            let y = [\n                0,\n                1,\n                1,\n                1\n            ];\n\n            // Logistic Regression function\n            function logisticRegression(X, y) {\n                let m = X.length;\n                let w = new Array(2).fill(0);\n                for (let i = 0; i < m; i++) {\n                    let sum = 0;\n                    for (let j = 0; j < X[i].length; j++) {\n                        sum += X[i][j] * w[j];\n                    }\n                    let prob = Math.exp(-sum) / (Math.exp(-sum) + 1);\n                    w.push(1 / m * (y[i] - 1) * prob);\n                }\n                return w;\n            }\n\n            // Train the model\n            let w = logisticRegression(X, y);\n\n            // Make predictions\n            function makePrediction(w, X) {\n                let predictions = new Array(X.length).fill(0);\n                for (let i = 0; i < X.length; i++) {\n                    let sum = 0;\n                    for (let j = 0; j < w.length; j++) {\n                        sum += X[i][j] * w[j];\n                    }\n                    let prob = Math.exp(-sum) / (Math.exp(-sum) + 1);\n                    predictions[i] = 1 if (prob > 0.5) else 0;\n                }\n                return predictions;\n            }\n\n            // Display the result\n            function displayResult(predictions) {\n                let result = document.getElementById(\"result\");\n                result.innerHTML = \"Predictions: \";\n                for (let i = 0; i < predictions.length; i++) {\n                    result.innerHTML += predictions[i] + \" \";\n                }\n            }\n\n            // Train and make predictions\n            let predictions = makePrediction(w, X);\n            displayResult(predictions);\n        </script>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>"
